<p>I am trying to set propertyitem to a png image by loading it in Image and then using SetPropertyItem. When I try to read it back using GetPropertyItem it says property not found. Whereas the same works when I use jpg image. Below is the code snippet,</p>  <pre><code>    static void AddProperty()     {             Image bmp = Image.FromFile("Pic.png");             PropertyItem newProperty = CreatePropertyItem();             newProperty.Id = 0x320;              newProperty.Type = 1;             newProperty.Value = new byte[] {55,22};             newProperty.Len = newProperty.Value.Length;               bmp.SetPropertyItem(newProperty);             bmp.Save("New.png");      }      static void GetProperty()     {         Image img = Image.FromFile("New.png");         PropertyItem p = img.GetPropertyItem(0x320);         Console.WriteLine("Received");     }      private static System.Drawing.Imaging.PropertyItem CreatePropertyItem()     {         var ci = typeof(System.Drawing.Imaging.PropertyItem);         var o = ci.GetConstructor(BindingFlags.NonPublic |      BindingFlags.Instance | BindingFlags.Public, null, new Type[] { }, null);          return (System.Drawing.Imaging.PropertyItem)o.Invoke(null);     }      static void Main(string[] args)     {         AddProperty();         GetProperty();     } </code></pre>  <p>I am getting System.ArgumentException with message "Property cannot be found." , So clearly the property is not saved in the new.png file.</p>